Salveo landed their last remaining shuttle atop the metal slab that
once was the Maximal Base.  The cargo ramp lowered and the crew walked
out into the scene of the disaster.  They were greeted by Lord Perseus
who stopped digging through debris to fill them in on what happened.

&quot;Right before the tidal wave hit, we saw a massive ship fly overhead,
not 300m above us.&quot; he said.  &quot;Something that massive falling from
orbit could easily explain the force of the water.&quot;

&quot;How&#39;s the rest of the city,&quot; asked Salveo.

&quot;Not good.  Most the people escaped to their shelters, however the
buildings were all destroyed.  Except the tower and several on the far
side of the island.&quot;

&quot;The shuttles?&quot;

&quot;Ours was destroyed, a few were in the air when the wave hit.&quot;

&quot;I dont think we can rebuild this.&quot; said Salveo after a moment of
looking at the devistation.

&quot;I think its possible, but unwise.  I think this gives us a new
opportunity to rejoin our Maximal allies and pool our resources.  So
for the moment, we should recover what we can and put it into the
shuttle, then assist Atlantis in anyway possible.&quot;

&quot;Rejoin Lord Elder?  Will that work?  And what about Atlantis?&quot;

&quot;Atlantis will be safe from the Unicronians; they wont bother with a
few hundred scientists and fisherman.  What they want is to destroy
us, and they will follow us wherever we decide to have our base.  As
for that crashed ship, I dont think its wise to mount a expedition
while the city lies in ruin and we remain baseless.&quot;

&quot;Right, so priority one, help the city and recover what we can from
our base.&quot; replied Salveo.

&quot;Correct.&quot;

