&gt;&gt; The engines had been losing power for the last day and a half; but finally
&gt;&gt; the gigantic craft could no longer fight the forces that pulled on it and
&gt;&gt; its orbit began to decay. Knowing that their only hope of survival was to
&gt;&gt; safely crash land, the pilot picked an open area of ocean and tried to
&gt;&gt; approach at a safe angle to slow itself enough to keep the ship intact.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Lord Perseus and his crew walked along the bridge that crossed the gap
&gt;&gt; between the part of the island where the hangers were located and the
&gt;&gt; peninsula area where the base sat. Suddenly the sky became dark and a
&gt;&gt; rumbling noise could be heard, growing louder and louder. He looked up to
&gt;&gt; see almost the whole sky occupied by a massive starship seemly heading
&gt;&gt; straight for the island. The Atlantis emergency alarm started to sound and
&gt;&gt; civilians rushed to their shelters.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; &quot;Everyone! To the base! Hurry!&quot; ordered Perseus breaking out into a run.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; The rumbling sound continued to get louder. As Perseus and his crew
&gt;&gt; reached
&gt;&gt; the base door, it was quickly opened for them then shut behind them. He
&gt;&gt; ordered everyone to move the lower level of the base. As the ship passed
&gt;&gt; over the island, the sound grew so loud that the ground shook and weaker
&gt;&gt; parts of buildings started to crumble, as in an earthquake. The ship
&gt;&gt; traveled for another three miles before it touched down in the deep ocean
&gt;&gt; waters. The force of the impact sent the ship hundreds of feet below the
&gt;&gt; surface and it continued to sink until coming to rest on the top of an
&gt;&gt; underwater mountain. The mass of water displaced by the ship started a
&gt;&gt; massive tsunami-like wave, going out in all directions.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; The ground began to shake again and the lights flickered inside the
&gt;&gt; Maximal
&gt;&gt; base.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; &quot;Sir, what&#39;s that noise?&quot; Guardia asked, sealing the last heavy door to
&gt;&gt; the
&gt;&gt; underground section of the base.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; The lights continued to flicker, then went out.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; At that moment the ten-story-high wall of water struck Atlantis from the
&gt;&gt; east, picking up all the boats in the harbor and tossing them onto the
&gt;&gt; land.
&gt;&gt; The parts of the docks that were not made of concrete were pushed up and
&gt;&gt; destroyed. A moment later the water hit the buildings in the lower wharf
&gt;&gt; area and they immediately collapsed under the intense weight of water.
&gt;&gt; Likewise the metal dome that made up the upper story of the Maximal base
&gt;&gt; was
&gt;&gt; immediately ripped from its foundations and carried away, along with
&gt;&gt; everything in the command center, the armory, mess hall, and the main bank
&gt;&gt; of CR chambers were also picked up and carried away.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; The lower floor of the base had a large metal slab to protect it from
&gt;&gt; bombing, and as the water continued to pour over it, everything on the
&gt;&gt; upper
&gt;&gt; floors was ripped away, leaving a clean plate of metal sitting at the
&gt;&gt; bottom
&gt;&gt; of the crater that was the base. The buildings along the center of the
&gt;&gt; town
&gt;&gt; were a little sturdier and remained standing, though heavily damaged. The
&gt;&gt; hanger and all the craft in it were picked up and thrown into the ocean.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; As the water came to tower it filled up the deep trench around the
&gt;&gt; structure
&gt;&gt; then the wall hit it, wrapping it entirely except for the top five
&gt;&gt; stories,
&gt;&gt; damaging supports, breaking out all the windows and destroying the bridges
&gt;&gt; that allowed access to the tower. The wave then continued across the rest
&gt;&gt; of the island, destroying buildings and carrying away the mass of debris,
&gt;&gt; and then all was eerily quiet.
